The White House Office of the First Lady has announced that Kristina Schake will be joining as Special Assistant to the President and Communications Director to the First Lady. Schake, who has extensive experience in child nutrition and community health issues, will bring valuable insight to the First Lady's work on childhood obesity and support for military families. She is the co-founder and principal of Griffin|Schake, a California-based public affairs and strategic communications firm, and has worked on various initiatives to bring about social change. Schake's previous roles include serving as the senior communications strategist for First Lady Maria Shriver and working on issues such as stem cell research and early childhood education. She was also the Director of the Governor's Summit on Obesity and the Communications Director for First 5 California. Schake is a graduate of Johns Hopkins University.